For greater accuracy, Becke introduced the well-established three-parameter scheme (B3, Eq. 
                  1.71

                ) [19], which is a more empirical model by relaxing the linear approximation. Heavily parameterized functionals (e.g., the M06 family of functionals [77, 78]) have appeared recently, which have push limits of the hybrid functionals, providing very high accuracy for a broad range of complex systems.

